"{\"uid\": \"express.co.uk-news-uk-1935203-olympic-gold-medals-only-worth\", \"text\": \"  Team GB's Olympic gold medal haul in Paris may be impressive, but the actual value of the precious metal in each one is surprisingly low - just \\u00a3408.59.  While the athletes were awarded 34 gold medals in total, the medals themselves are not made of solid gold. Instead, they are composed of at least 92.5% silver and coated with a minimum of six grams of pure gold.  At the current gold price of \\u00a31,903.45 per ounce, the solid gold content in each medal is worth a mere \\u00a3408.59. This means the total value of the pure gold in Team GB's 34 gold medals amounts to just \\u00a313,892.06.  Do not miss:Tom Daley announces retirement in emotional statement days after Olympic success  In contrast, if the gold medals were made of solid gold like they were the last time the Olympics were held in Paris in 1924, their value would be staggering.  A single solid gold medal weighing 529 grams would be worth \\u00a335,962 at today's prices. And the 34 gold medals won by British athletes would contain a total of \\u00a31.22 million worth of gold.  \\\"The value of Team GB's Olympic gold medals may not be worth their weight in solid gold, but their significance is immeasurable,\\\" said Cameron Parry, CEO of gold savings app TallyMoney.  Do not miss:France star only player in squad denied Olympic medal due to little-known rule  Do not miss:Recreate Princess Kate's beloved stripy top look for less than \\u00a330 at M&S  Do not miss:Piers Morgan's stinging ten-word Olympics verdict as he slams LA handover  The dramatic increase in the value of gold since 1924 - a rise of 44,864% - underscores just how little precious metal is actually in the medals awarded to today's Olympians.  \\\"This dramatic rise not only highlights gold's resilience and value appreciation over time, but also adds a fascinating layer to the achievements of our athletes,\\\" Parry added.  We use your sign-up to provide content in ways you have consented to and to improve our understanding of you. This may include adverts from us and 3rd parties based on our understanding. You can unsubscribe at any time. Read ourPrivacy Policy  While the medals may not be as valuable as they once were, the accomplishments of the British athletes who won them remain priceless.  SEARCH  CONNECT WITH US  TODAY'S PAPER  See today's front and back pages, download the newspaper, order back issues and use the historic Daily Express newspaper archive.  EXPRESS.CO.UK  Daily Express uses notifications to keep you updated\"}"